findings.title: Wrong argument count for function call: 2 arguments given but expected 1
findings.description: The function call has an incorrect number of arguments, which can lead to unexpected behavior or errors.

findings.title: Potential modification or alteration of smart contract functions when owner address is active
findings.description: When the smart contract has an active owner address, some of the smart contract functions can be edited, modified or altered.

findings.title: Lack of ReentrancyGuard to prevent reentrant calls to a function
findings.description: Cure Token’s staking contract does not utilize “ReentrancyGuard” to prevent reentrant calls to a function.
